Footballer, William Troost-Ekong, has announced his exit from club, Watford FC. He made the announcement on Monday via his Instagram account. The Nigerian defender said, “The moment has come for me to move on from #watfordfcofficial after three special seasons shared with everyone involved. From everyone at the restaurant, security workers, volunteers at the stadium to the medical & office staff and all the rest you have made my time what it was. The coaches and most of all my teammates, I can only say thank you!!! ALSO READ: Footballer Dani Alves arrested after being accused of sexual assault “The Pozzo family for believing in me and the important five years of my career at both clubs with the highlight the promotion and a chance to achieve my boyhood dream of playing in the Premier League.” He is set to join Serie A club, Salernitana, in coming days. 